1 olive oil
1 bag herbs
1 packet walnuts
1 bag slaw mix
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise
1 apple

Thinly slice apple into half-moons. Pick and thinly slice herbs. Roughly
chop walnuts.

Heat a medium frying pan over medium-high heat. Toast walnuts, tossing,
until golden, 3-4 minutes.

In a large bowl, combine apple, herbs, slaw mix and dill & parsley
mayonnaise. Season with salt and pepper.

Transfer the apple and herb slaw to a serving bowl. Top with toasted walnuts
to serve.